  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Later on, as the wave of war moved, and the Germans realized that the war is not going to last to their victory, they relaxed a bit.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And also some of the old SS men who started building the camp were move to fronts, either west front or east front.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So the change, wave changed.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I've seen people being thrown into the latrine, where they were drowned in-- in, you know, the dirt.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I've seen also people being hung for contact with civilian population or any other reason which they could-- could have-- if they started stealing some stuff from magazines.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "In some cases, they used to treat them as saboteurs and hung them.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There was also-- there was also-- one day, I remember, two Polish officers were trying to escape.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The Lagerkommandant brought them into the-- in front of everybody during a roll call.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And gave them-- one received 100 lashes and the other 150.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And then they were sent to the-- to be-- penalty company to be left for dead after not being given any food.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So that was something.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I couldn't understand why the Lagerkommandant gave so many to show that these people were trying to escape, and that's the reason they were beaten.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Many times, when companies used to come back from work, and there were some people who tried to escape, they were shot.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They used to leave-- leave them in front of the camp, so that everybody entering the gate could see six, eight, 10 people lying down who tried to escape.",
      "word_count": 29
    }
  ],
